    <item>
      <title>Benchmark write speed</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/linux/benchmark_write_speed/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Feb 2023 14:12:45 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/linux/benchmark_write_speed/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;-benchmark-write-speed-to-a-disk&#34;&gt;&#xA;  💾 Benchmark Write Speed to a Disk&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#-benchmark-write-speed-to-a-disk&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Sometimes you need to test how fast a (network) disk can handle writes.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A common method is:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Write &lt;strong&gt;one large file&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Split it into &lt;strong&gt;many small files&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Benchmark copying them using &lt;code&gt;rsync&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;cp&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Why?&#xA;Some storage systems handle large sequential writes very well, but struggle with many small files (metadata overhead, IOPS limits, etc.).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Date command in bash</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/linux/date_command/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Feb 2023 14:12:45 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/linux/date_command/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;just-a-small-example-of-the-date-command&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Just a small example of the date command&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;heading-link&#34; href=&#34;#just-a-small-example-of-the-date-command&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;i class=&#34;fa-solid fa-link&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34; title=&#34;Link to heading&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&#xA;    &lt;span class=&#34;sr-only&#34;&gt;Link to heading&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Show the weekday in number, always handy to know, small examples of the date command&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# Display weekday&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;date +%u&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;# Display quater of the year&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;date +%q&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8b949e;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;#!/bin/bash&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#79c0ff&#34;&gt;todayWeekday&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;date +%u&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#79c0ff&#34;&gt;todayQuater&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;date +%q&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ff7b72&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo -e &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a5d6ff&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;The command &amp;#34;date +%u&amp;#34; gives the weekday in numbers output is:&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#79c0ff&#34;&gt;$todayWeekday&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
